{
  "name": "dct-microsoft-media-center-rollout-2002-08",
  "title": "Microsoft Rolls Out Media Center",
  "description": "News analysis of Microsoft's announcement of Windows XP Media Center Edition \u2014 a living-room PC variant combining TV tuner, hardware video encoder, and infrared remote, first demoed at CES 2002 under the 'Freestyle' codename. HP, NEC, and Samsung are the launch OEMs; Kastner frames the offering as the strongest PC-in-the-living-room push to date while noting Windows task-scheduling vulnerabilities and competition from SonicBlue and TiVo.",
